  ('reading', '2', 2, '2.main', 'ELA.2.R.2', 'Read: "Ben woke up early. He packed his bag, ate breakfast, and walked to school." What is this story mostly about?', '["Ben going to sleep","Ben playing a game","Ben at the beach","Ben getting ready for school"]', 3, 'All the details are about Ben getting ready for school — that is the main idea.', 10),
  ('reading', '2', 2, '2.main', 'ELA.2.R.2', 'Read: "Bees buzz from flower to flower. They carry pollen. This helps new plants grow." What is the main idea?', '["Bees are yellow","Bees are scary","Bees help plants grow","Bees live in trees"]', 2, 'The passage explains how bees help new plants grow.', 10),
  ('reading', '2', 2, '2.main', 'ELA.2.R.2', 'Read: "First, Lia mixed the flour and eggs. Next, she poured the batter. Last, she baked the cake." What did Lia do FIRST?', '["Baked the cake","Poured the batter","Ate the cake","Mixed the flour and eggs"]', 3, 'The word "First" tells us she mixed the flour and eggs to start.', 10),
